": "42048"}, {"t": "That's a Plenty", "c": "Lew Pollack", "w": "11365"}, {"t": "Royal Garden Blues", "c": "Spencer Williams", "w": "40189"}, {"t": "Keeping Out of Mischief Now", "c": "Fats Waller", "w": "53334"}]}], "works_created": [], "quotes": [], "about_quotes": [{"speaker": "Cliff Leeman", "relation": "played with", "confidence": 1.0, "evidence": "To get back to the Condon band, when I went in with Eddie in '51... And we played with that band", "doc_title": "68087_Cliff Leeman oral history interview", "collection": "rutgers", "url": "https://rucore.libraries.rutgers.edu/rutgers-lib/68087/"}, {"speaker": "Vincent Pelote", "relation": "knows of", "confidence": 1.0, "evidence": "Eddie Condon was my hero. I loved Eddie Condon for just sitting there and doing that...", "doc_title": "Vincent Pelote interviewed by Monk Rowe, Orlando, Florida, February 25, 2017", "collection": "hamilton", "url": "https://litsdigital.hamilton.edu/collections/object/vincent-pelote-interviewed-monk-rowe-orlando-florida-february-25-2017"}, {"speaker": "Wild Bill Davison", "relation": "in music group with", "confidence": 0.95, "evidence": "if you want to join him here, that's all right too... they joined us there... Eddie liked my mellophone and he used to feature me on the mellophone", "doc_title": "63519_Wild Bill Davison oral history interview", "collection": "rutgers", "url": "https://rucore.libraries.rutgers.edu/rutgers-lib/63519/"}, {"speaker": "George Wein", "relation": "collaborated with", "confidence": 0.95, "evidence": "the first evening that I produced at Newport, I had Eddie Condon with Bobby Hackett and Wild Bill Davison and Pee Wee Russell and a few others", "doc_title": "George Wein — Smithsonian Jazz Oral History", "collection": "si", "url": "https://amhistory.si.edu/jazz/Wein-George/Wein_George_Transcript.pdf"}, {"speaker": "Sharkey Bonano", "relation": "in music group with", "confidence": 0.95, "evidence": "So we got Farz, Ben Pollack was on the drums... Eddie Condon played the guitar. ... So to make a long story short, we made a session", "doc_title": "Sharkey Bonano Interview, 1966-11-09", "collection": "tulane", "url": "https://library.search.tulane.edu/permalink/01TUL_INST/4h6sc4/alma9945523735806326"}, {"speaker": "Johnny Varro", "relation": "collaborated with", "confidence": 0.95, "evidence": "I got a call from Eddie Condon to work his saloon, as a soloist. Actually it was a duo with Buzzy Drootin on drums and myself.", "doc_title": "Johnny Varro interviewed by Monk Rowe, Clearwater Beach, Florida, March 16, 2001", "collection": "hamilton", "url": "https://litsdigital.hamilton.edu/collections/object/johnny-varro-interviewed-monk-rowe-clearwater-beach-florida-march-16-2001"}]}